Descriptor.0: RPW-LFR-SURV-BP2> RPW Low Frequency Receiver Basic parameters set 2 data in Survey mode

TEXT.0: This file contains RPW LFR level 2R Survey BP2 data of the current test.

Logical_source_description.0: Solar Orbiter Radio and Plasma Wave, Level 2 Low Frequency Receiver (LFR) Basic Parameter Set 2 (BP2) Data in Survey Mode

Rules_of_use.0: Data provided are publicly available. If used in presentations or publications, please acknowledge Solar Orbiter/RPW Investigation (M. Maksimovic, PIs). Please read carefully the caveats attached to the data. For reporting purposes, we request bibliography information for any publication, etc., using these data. Please send information on the use of this data to: M. Maksimovic (PI).

Acknowledgement.0: The authors are pleased to acknowledge the Solar Orbiter/RPW Investigation (M. Maksimovic, PIs) for access to data.

CAL_ENTITY_AFFILIATION.1: Laboratoire de Physique et de Chimie del'Environnement et de l'Espace (LPC2E)

CAL_ENTITY_AFFILIATION.2: Swedish Institute of Space Physics, Uppsala

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Flag to indicate if the receiver in the SURVEY_BURST (=1) or SURVEY_NORMAL (=0) mode

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Sampling frequency of the BP2

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Index to indicate the sampling frequency of the BP2 : F0, F1 or F2 in order to use only one skeleton for the 3 normal mode bp2 products of ICD.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Copy of multiplexer setting.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Indicates the mode of BIAS multiplexer for a set of BP2 parameters. Possible values are 0 : Standard operation. 1 : Probe 1 fails. 2 : Probe 2 fails. 3 : Probe 3 fails. 4 : Calibration mode 0. 5 : Calibration mode 1. 6 : Calibration mode 2. 7 : Calibration mode 3.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Copy of enable/disable HV (+- 100V).

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Indicates the status of BIAS HV. Possible values are DISABLED = 0. ENABLED = 1.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Copy of enable/disable BIAS 1.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Indicates the status of BIAS probe 1. Possible values are DISABLED = 0. ENABLED = 1.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Copy of enable/disable BIAS 2.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Indicates the status of BIAS probe 2. Possible values are DISABLED = 0. ENABLED = 1.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Copy of enable/disable BIAS 3.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Indicates the status of BIAS probe 3. Possible values are DISABLED = 0. ENABLED = 1.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Copy of BIAS status.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Indicates the status of BIAS. Possible values are OFF = 0 - Power line off. ON = 1 - Power line on.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: BIAS Works/BIAS Fails configuration.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Flag to indicate if the local time is synchronized with the RPW DPU clock or not. Possible values: synchronized=0, not synchronized=1. This flag is extracted from ACQUISITION_TIME in L0 packets, it is the MSB of the CUC time.
